\fs24\fsmilli12012 Now we briefly describe the RRT*\
-Smart algorithm along with the two proposed key concepts:\
Intelligent Sampling and Path Optimization. Initially, random search of the state space takes\
place as RRT* does until the first path is found. Once this initial path is found, it works to\
optimize this path by interconnecting the directly visible nodes in this path. Biasing points for\
intelligent sampling are yielded from this optimized path. At these biasing points, sampling\
takes place at regular intervals, which are governed by a constant 
\f2\i\fs24\fsmilli12011 b 
\f1\i0\fs24\fsmilli12012 that in turn depends upon\
the biasing ratio explained later. As the algorithm progresses, this process continues and the\
path keeps on being optimized. The biasing shifts towards the new path whenever a shorter path\
is found. Algorithm 2 outlines this process.\

